The paper deals with algorithms and lower bounds for a classic problem in data structures (3SUM) and its preprocessing variant (3SUM-Indexing), which are both central topics in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a novel formulation of a problem in cryptography, which falls under the category of cryptographic protocols (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its results for the design of backdoored random oracles, which is a topic in the intersection of cryptography (cs.CR) and complexity theory (cs.CY).
